<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="313" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1873,2006]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1436,151,501]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="313" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1909,1934]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">Remarks.</emphasis>
we are naming tripods and tetrapods the large triactines and tetractines with stout actines that are located on the external tubes. As shown by Klautau 
<emphasis box="[795,850,1945,1969]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">et al</emphasis>
. (2016), the shape of tripods varies even inside individuals, from characteristic ones with stout actines and raised centre to just large triactines. Those authors assigned this variability to polymorphism or plasticity. As we have already observed several times this variability in individuals of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klautau" authorityYear="2017" box="[343,452,189,212]" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[343,452,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Borojevia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we agree with them and decided to name tripods and tetrapods the large triactines and tetractines present on the external tubes of 
<taxonomicName authority="Klautau, 2017" authorityName="Klautau" authorityYear="2017" box="[665,839,224,248]" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="tenuispinata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[665,839,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">B. tenuispinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[851,946,223,248]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[851,946,223,248]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
. Because of the special position of these spicules in the cormus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klautau" authorityYear="2017" box="[443,552,261,284]" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[443,552,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Borojevia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, we think they are a different spicule category, not homologous to the triactines and tetractines found inside it.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
Six species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klautau" authorityYear="2017" box="[376,485,333,356]" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[376,485,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Borojevia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are currently recognised: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Klautau, Sole-Cava &amp; Borojevic, 1994)" authorityName="Klautau, Sole-Cava &amp; Borojevic" authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Klautau, Sole-Cava &amp; Borojevic" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[797,1395,332,357]" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="aspina">
<emphasis box="[797,907,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">B. aspina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Klautau" box="[927,1388,332,357]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Klautau, M., Sole-Cava, A. &amp; Borojevic, R. (1994) Biochemical systematics of sibling sympatric species of Clathrina (Porifera, Calcarea). Biochemical Systematics and Ecology, 22, 367 - 375. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / 0305 - 1978 (94) 90027 - 2" type="journal article" year="1994">Klautau, Solé-Cava &amp; Borojevic, 1994</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sole-Cava et al., 1991)" authorityName="Sole-Cava et al." authorityYear="1991" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">B. brasiliensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sole-Cava" box="[304,586,367,392]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Sole-Cava, A. M., Klautau, M., Boury-Esnault, N., Borojevic, R. &amp; Thorpe, J. (1991) Genetic evidence for cryptic speciation in allopatric populations of two cosmopolitan species of the calcareous sponge Clathrina. Marine Biology, 111, 381 - 386. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 01319410" type="journal article" year="1991">
Solé-Cava 
<emphasis box="[438,495,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">et al</emphasis>
., 1991
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Haeckel, 1872)" authorityName="Haeckel" authorityYear="1872" baseAuthorityName="Haeckel" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[615,970,367,392]" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cerebrum">
<emphasis box="[615,761,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">B. cerebrum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Haeckel" box="[786,962,367,392]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Haeckel, E. (1872) Die Kalkschwamme. Eine Monographie in zwei Banden Text und einem Atlas mit 60 Tafeln Abbildungen. Fol. 1 - 3. G. Reimer, Berlin, 484 pp., 418 pp. &amp; 60 pp." type="book chapter" year="1872">Haeckel, 1872</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Klautau et al., 2016" authorityName="Klautau et al." authorityYear="2016" box="[990,1391,367,392]" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="croatica">
<emphasis box="[990,1123,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">B. croatica</emphasis>
Klautau 
<emphasis box="[1244,1303,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">et al</emphasis>
., 2016
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Austin, 1996)" authorityName="Austin" authorityYear="1996" baseAuthorityName="Austin" baseAuthorityYear="1996" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="paracerebrum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">B. paracerebrum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Austin" box="[329,483,404,429]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Austin, W. C. (1996) Sponges from Rocas Alijos. In: Schmieder, R. W. (Ed.), Monographiae Biologicae. Rocas Alijos. Scientific Results from the Cordell Expeditions. Fol. 75. Kluwer Academic Publishers, Dordrecht, Boston, London, pp. 237 - 256. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 017 - 2917 - 8 _ 17" type="journal article" year="1996">Austin, 1996</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Klautau &amp; Valentine, 2003)" authorityName="Klautau &amp; Valentine" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Klautau &amp; Valentine" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[557,1085,404,429]" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="tetrapodifera">
<emphasis box="[557,740,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">B. tetrapodifera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Klautau" box="[759,1077,404,429]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Klautau, M. &amp; Valentine, C. (2003) Revision of the genus Clathrina (Porifera, Calcarea). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 139, 1 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 0024 - 4082.2003.00063. x" type="journal article" year="2003">Klautau &amp; Valentine, 2003</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Only 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Klautau &amp; Valentine" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[1167,1350,404,428]" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="tetrapodifera">
<emphasis box="[1167,1350,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">B. tetrapodifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Klautau, 2017" authorityName="Klautau" authorityYear="2017" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="tenuispinata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">B. tenuispinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[300,392,439,464]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[300,392,439,464]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
have tetrapods, however, differently from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Klautau &amp; Valentine" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[891,1073,440,464]" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="tetrapodifera">
<emphasis box="[891,1073,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">B. tetrapodifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the new species does not have many tetrapods. Besides, the apical actine of the tetrapods has spines while in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Klautau &amp; Valentine" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[1027,1206,476,500]" class="Calcarea" family="Clathrinidae" genus="Borojevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="tetrapodifera">
<emphasis box="[1027,1206,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">B. tetrapodifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is smooth.
</paragraph>
